  "text": "When comparing the above-described glucose disposal results with our previous measurements in AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ and Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice, we found that in tissues in which only AS160 or Tbc1d1 is predominantly expressed, such as brown adipose tissue or tibialis anterior muscles, respectively, changes in glucose uptake in AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice were similar to the ones observed previously in AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ (17) and Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice [CITATION_1] . In gastrocnemius muscle, which expresses both Rab GAPs well [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , the changes in AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice mix the findings obtained with single-knockout mice. Glucose uptake in AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ gastrocnemius is decreased under basal conditions and does not increase in response to insulin [CITATION_5] . Tbc1d1",
